text: The pug-nosed shrub frog (Pseudophilautus silus) is a frog. It lives in the middle of Sri Lanka on the Horton Plains plateau and other places where the tree branches come together like a roof. People have seen it between 1550 and 1600 meters above sea level. ==First paper== * ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia
title: Pseudophilautus silus
